1
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:06,880
Maybe I'm drawn to you.

2
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:10,280
But if you're Sakura,

3
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,280
I have to kill this feeling.

4
00:00:14,060 --> 00:00:16,250
(Undelusional precepts)

5
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:17,500
Answer me.

6
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:20,700
Are you really Hanaoka Nao?

7
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:22,360
Or

8
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:25,780
Sakura?

9
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:29,860
It was my first love.

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
If it were true, it would be a dream come true.

11
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:37,840
I'm so happy I could cry.

12
00:00:41,340 --> 00:00:42,660
We are

13
00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:45,400
normal.

14
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:49,740
That was Sakura's mother.

15
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,120
I don't know anything about it.

16
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:55,220
(Dear Nao, I didn't do it.)
I was just making sweets...

17
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:02,680
(Undelusional precepts)
I've come prepared.

18
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:07,780
He's ready to go to hell.

19
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:14,220
My name is Hanaoka Nao.

20
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:16,740
I'm not Sakura.

21
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,360
Do I look so much alike?

22
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:25,740
I'm with a girl called Sakura.

23
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,860
Sakura hid in the shadows.

24
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:33,360
She was always so shy.

25
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,400
Like this...

26
00:01:39,860 --> 00:01:41,900
She never looked at me straight in the eye.

27
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,740
I like the way you look at me.

28
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:53,680
Nao, I believe in you.

29
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:58,500
But we don't do this kind of thing anymore...

30
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,780
If you don't like it, you can shake it off.

31
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,640
I want it all to be mine.

32
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,640
That's about it.

33
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:12,200
I love you now.

34
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,720
Mom, forgive me just for now.

35
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,260
I'm really out of my mind.

36
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,200
What is waiting for me?

37
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,240
Even though there is only hell.

38
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,100
I can't

39
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:38,840
shake it off.

40
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:40,820
Tsubaki.

41
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:47,180
What's wrong with me?

42
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,780
In the arms of Tsubaki,

43
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,680
I can't believe I'm happy.

44
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,300
(Takaragawa)

45
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,620
Is it morning already?

46
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,220
Yes.

47
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,280
It's been a long time since I slept so well.

48
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,860
That's weird.

49
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,560
Honesty,

50
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,120
I don't know how to do it well.

51
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,500
But...

52
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,840
I'll take care of it in my own way.

53
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,000
You're lying to me...

54
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,900
It's a fake marriage...

55
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:57,820
(Kougetsu)
This...

56
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,700
Kougetsuan's work clothes.

57
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,720
You're going to be a part of this family.

58
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,460
The uniform my mom used to wear.

59
00:04:18,780 --> 00:04:20,040
Nao-san.

60
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:24,040
Can you get me four teas at 10 o'clock?

61
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,940
I have a very important guest.

62
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,680
I understand.

63
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:35,080
What? How dare the landlady bring me out in public?

64
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,220
(Hamabe Minami)

65
00:04:52,940 --> 00:04:54,220
(Yohohama Ryusei)

66
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:59,580
=Cursed in Love=

67
00:05:19,740 --> 00:05:21,160
Please excuse us.

68
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:27,420
This air, she is trying to check me.

69
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:29,020
We have brought you some tea.

70
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,980
Serve it to you.

71
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:32,940
Yes.

72
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:36,700
Don't worry, I at least know how to serve tea.

73
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:42,840
Thank you.

74
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:44,240
Please excuse me.

75
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,860
Good, perfect.

76
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,480
Please wait.

77
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:52,660
Can you stay there in case I still need you?

78
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:54,700
Yes.

79
00:05:56,720 --> 00:06:00,240
Kyoko-san, that kimono
is summer Oshima, isn't it?

80
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,360
Yes.

81
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,540
I prefer weaving.

82
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:08,880
It's beautiful! I don't think I could afford it.

83
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,860
No, no, not at all.

84
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:14,140
Um... Um...

85
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:15,880
Would you like me to change your tea?

86
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,620
Hey, you...

87
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,380
I'm so sorry.

88
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:25,820
I am very sorry.

89
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:31,760
I'm not sure.

90
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:35,900
You really don't know, do you?

91
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:39,700
"Would you like me to change your tea?"

92
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:43,040
It means, "It's time for you to go away".

93
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,080
Didn't they tell you that?

94
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,800
To that mother.

95
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,600
I'm sorry.

96
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:53,120
But my mother had nothing to do with it.

97
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:56,600
Because of one ignorant and stupid comment.

98
00:06:56,880 --> 00:07:00,640
Everything we've built up over the years
can come crashing down in an instant.

99
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:04,000
That's the world we live in!

100
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,920
You don't deserve to wear this.

101
00:07:10,580 --> 00:07:11,880
Take off your clothes!

102
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,340
If you are not well brought up

103
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:24,580
and you don't even know what this world is.

104
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,760
So, you and Tsubaki-san can be together?

105
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,440
Do you want to get married?

106
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,040
Shallow.

107
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,680
You really have the nerve!

108
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,940
It's not too late.

109
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,940
For Tsubaki,

110
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:47,060
you have to leave as soon as possible!

111
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:53,220
A different world.

112
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:56,880
No matter how much passion I have for sweets.

113
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,200
I can't help it.

114
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,920
They deny everything about me.

115
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:12,380
Nao-san! You're done for the day.

116
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:13,640
Jojima-kun.

117
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,540
Could you come with me for a moment?

118
00:08:21,420 --> 00:08:23,920
Afternoon tea!

119
00:08:24,660 --> 00:08:26,640
I didn't want to come alone.

120
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:28,460
Come on, let's eat.

121
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,880
Enjoy yourself.

122
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:36,600
Delicious!

123
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,460
And fun!

124
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,600
It goes well with alcohol and coffee.

125
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,560
Indeed!

126
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:44,700
You can put seasonal items here.

127
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:45,500
For example?

128
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,920
Tanabata-style!

129
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,480
That's a good idea.

130
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:53,640
With Jojima-kun, I can talk purely about wagashi.

131
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,040
It's a real relief.

132
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:59,200
I knew it was a waste of time
to become a landlady.

133
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:03,780
You can't make sweets
when you are the proprietress of Kougetsuan.

134
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,700
I like it so much.

135
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:09,140
Jojima-kun is going to take over
your family's shop.

136
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,960
You'll remember me, won't you?

137
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:15,000
A small shop in Noto,
but the taste is the best in Ishikawa!

138
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:17,440
No, it's the best in the country.

139
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,440
The warabi is a speciality.

140
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:22,280
It's plump and flaky.

141
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,500
Plump and flaky?

142
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,780
I want to eat!

143
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,100
Would you like to come and eat?

144
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:29,660
In my room.

145
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,800
What?

146
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,020
It was just sent to me from my parents' house.

147
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:35,020
Jojima-kun's room?

148
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:38,820
Oh, I don't think Nao-san knows.

149
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,760
The employees' rooms are separated.

150
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,920
It's the farthest corner room.

151
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,000
That room...

152
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:52,780
I don't know what I'm talking about.

153
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:56,100
"In the room." I'm sorry.

154
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,220
Are you sure?

155
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:01,060
Can I go?

156
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:07,920
Well... I'll wait for you tonight.

157
00:10:16,380 --> 00:10:16,980
(Takatsuki)

158
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:18,240
(Takatsuki)
Excuse me.

159
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,280
Time for your medication.

160
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:26,400
Are you all right?

161
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,420
Don't get the wrong idea.

162
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:35,400
I don't recognize you as my successor.

163
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:41,380
That boy... that boy.

164
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,300
Find me quickly.

165
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,900
I've always wanted to go back.

166
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:59,880
But I can't remember where it was.

167
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:16,740
Definitely.

168
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:23,300
This is the room.

169
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:34,620
Nao.

170
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,260
Are you looking for Nao?

171
00:11:50,340 --> 00:11:53,120
I'm sorry, I left the window open.

172
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:57,060
I'll close it then.

173
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:58,860
The window,

174
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:01,460
it's not set up properly
and needs to be floated once.

175
00:12:01,460 --> 00:12:02,480
It won't close.

176
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,720
How did you know?

177
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:06,920
My room was the same as yours.

178
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:11,280
I thought the main house was in order.

179
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,880
Oh, no, I've got to be careful.

180
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:18,480
Oh, this flower...

181
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,520
Gardenias, right?

182
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,800
Yes, gardenias.

183
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,420
Because the fruit does not
split spontaneously when ripe.

184
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:28,380
The name of the gardenia is "no mouth".

185
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,080
You know a lot about it.

186
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,480
My mother likes it.

187
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:35,980
As the seasons change,

188
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:39,740
I would give my father
ideas for sweets with those flowers.

189
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:43,720
I see.

190
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,160
That's my dream, too.

191
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:49,020
We thought about it a lot as a couple.

192
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:53,320
We want to make sure that
every single customer has a smile on their face.

193
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:59,560
It's small, but the warmth is second to none.

194
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:03,280
I think that dream is very good.

195
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,560
I want it to happen.

196
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,840
He has that "me too" look on his face.

197
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:10,040
What?

198
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,120
But,

199
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,160
Tsubaki-san is different, isn't he?

200
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:20,560
♪Happy to win, Hanaichimonme.♪

201
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:26,560
♪It's a shame to lose, Hanaichimonme.♪

202
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:32,580
♪The lady next door, come here for a minute.♪

203
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:38,140
♪I'm too scared of the demons to go.♪

204
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:47,480
I overheard Tsubaki-san saying goodbye before.

205
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:52,400
"What's in it for you? I said."

206
00:13:57,060 --> 00:14:00,940
You can't be happy with Tsubaki-san.

207
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:05,880
I know, that is the one.

208
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,900
Why not with me?

209
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:12,900
♪I want her.♪

210
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:15,600
♪I don't know if she's the one.♪

211
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:21,180
♪I want this girl I want this girl I don't know.♪

212
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:25,040
Tsubaki-san...

213
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,260
If you've got time to mess with
other people's stuff,

214
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:29,260
why don't you practice your incrustation?

215
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:32,920
Sorry, I...

216
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,680
I like Nao-san.

217
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:39,040
Tsubaki!

218
00:14:47,740 --> 00:14:48,240
Come on.

219
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,040
What do you like about her? That normal girl.

220
00:14:58,740 --> 00:14:59,740
Hey!

221
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:02,640
Why did you go to that room?

222
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:07,260
Tsubaki-san, why did you do that to Jojima-kun?

223
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:09,400
I'm pissed off. I don't have a choice.

224
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:12,180
It's not true that Jojima likes me...

225
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,180
If that were the case, it would be even worse.

226
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,120
Stay away from him.

227
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:28,500
Jojima-kun.

228
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:31,320
You shouldn't talk to me.

229
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,480
He's going to be angry with me again.

230
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,920
But it's my job to wash the dishes.

231
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:38,120
Jojima-kun needs to prepare the red beans.

232
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:38,940
It's okay.

233
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:42,600
I'm quitting at the end of next month.

234
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:43,600
Eh?

235
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:50,000
Tsubaki-san! Why is Jojima-kun being sacked?

236
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,880
Please don't do that.

237
00:15:52,460 --> 00:15:53,120
Fired?

238
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,380
I can't believe you made him quit.

239
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:58,450
(Hanaoka Nao's mother is a killer.)
I'm sorry, but can you quit my shop?

240
00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:00,340
I'm sorry, but can you quit my shop?

241
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:03,100
Please.

242
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:07,040
You're very desperate.

243
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,740
Jojima has a dream to take over his parents' shop.

244
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,560
Then it's better to give up early.

245
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,880
He still can't even cook red beans properly.

246
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:14,420
He has no taste.

247
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:15,100
So now...

248
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,360
Kougetsuan is not the place to talk about dreams!

249
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,820
We don't want people who don't benefit the shop.

250
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:24,520
I heard Tsubaki-san talking about
leaving you before.

251
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,260
"What's in it for the shop?"

252
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:39,260
This is it!

253
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,160
It's too early for me.

254
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:51,460
Again... Tsubaki-san is far away.

255
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:06,800
You've done a great job.

256
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:11,420
Just so you know, I'm only here for one thing.

257
00:17:11,420 --> 00:17:13,700
It's about destroying your son.

258
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:17,620
He's not going to be crushed easily.

259
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:21,500
Well, you can do what you like.

260
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:22,780
But...

261
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:27,180
You have to stop them getting married, I swear!

262
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,260
If that's what it takes,

263
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,880
you don't care if your son gets hurt.

264
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,700
You're really scary.

265
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:41,380
Oh, the smell of red beans cooking.

266
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:46,940
I...don't like this smell.

267
00:17:54,660 --> 00:17:56,380
Tsubaki and Nao...

268
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,820
They've been having a row about you.

269
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,240
Really?

270
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,240
What do you mean?

271
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,340
He said he wanted to
take over his family's business.

272
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:08,260
The shop didn't go under a year ago, did it?

273
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,400
No, Yamaguchi-san.

274
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:14,200
